Recommends: pandoc, libreoffice, ghostscript, tesseract-ocr, qpdf
Description: Universal document format converter
 Shift is a powerful command-line tool for converting between document formats,
 compressing PDFs, extracting text via OCR, and more. Supports batch processing,
 multiple quality levels, and integrations with external tools like Pandoc,
 LibreOffice, wkhtmltopdf, and Tesseract.
 .
 Commands installed:
  - shift-convert: Convert documents between formats
  - shift-compress: Reduce PDF file sizes
  - shift-pages: Remove/split/analyze PDF pages
  - shift-edit: Advanced PDF editing (GUI and CLI)
  - shift-ocr: Extract text from scanned PDFs/images
 .
 Run `shift-convert --help` or `shift --help` to get started.
